<paragraphs>
    <title>The Ferris Wheel Again</title>
<p>
  The Brown County Ferris Wheel has diameter <m>50</m> meters and completes one full revolution every two minutes.  When you are at the lowest point on the wheel, you are still <m>5</m> meters above the ground.    
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
           What is your height above the ground when the angle <m>\theta</m>, measured from the <m>3</m> o'clock position is <m>30^{\circ}</m>? It may be helpful to draw a picture of the ferris wheel.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
            Assume that you board the ferris wheel from a platform at its lowest point when <m>t=0</m>. Given that the ferris wheel rotates at a constant speed, find a formula for the angle <m>\theta</m>, measured from the <m>3</m> o'clock position, as a function of <m>t</m>.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
           Use your answer to part (c) to find a formula for your height above the ground as a function of <m>t</m>.
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>

</paragraphs>   



